    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>There is a marriage fest going on in the String Land. Now every String wants to look good for<br />\ntheir king Studd. But king Studd only likes <b>Palindromes</b>. Help him find his true love.</p>\n<p>Your best friend String S comes to you for help as it wants to become a Palindrome. The String S consists of lowercase alphabets only.\n</p>\n<p>Your task is to convert it into a Palindrome by changing(may be not) some of the letters into other. You can convert a letter S[i] (1 &lt;= i &lt;= size of S) into any other letter but with a fixed cost associated with that letter and for each letter this cost is given to you.</p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The first line of the input contains an integer <b>T</b> denoting the number of test cases.<br />\nThe description of <b>T</b> test cases follows.</p>\n<p>The first line of each test case contains the string <b>S</b>.<br />\nNext line contains <b>26</b> integers, the <b>cost</b> of lower case english alphabets (a,b,...z).</p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For each test case,Print a single line consisting of the minimum cost to convert the Input string</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b><b> \u2264 </b><b>T</b><b> \u2264 </b><b>10</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b><b> \u2264 </b><b>|S|</b><b> \u2264 </b><b>100000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b><b> \u2264 </b><b>cost</b><b> \u2264 </b><b>10000</b></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n<p>2\nabc\n1 6 3 2 4 5 3 6 7 6 5 4 5 6 3 2 7 5 4 3 2 5 7 8 9 9\nabca\n2 6 3 2 4 5 3 6 7 6 5 4 5 6 3 2 7 5 4 3 2 5 7 8 9 4\n</p>\n<b>Output:</b>\n<p>1\n3</p>\n</pre><h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Case 1</b>:convert 'a' to 'c' with a cost of 1 to make the given string a palindrome.<br />\n<b>Case 2</b>:convert 'c' to 'b' with a cost of 3 to make the given string a palindrome</p>\n",
